				<div class="postbody">
				As we all know the race to a better processor is heating up, AMD has released the Opteron 64 bit processor, however Pentium will release it's Hyperthreading P4 processor first quarter of 2005.
<br />

<br />
So my question is.. 
<br />

<br />
For gaming, which will be better the AMD 64 or the P4?
<br />

<br />
I currently know that Windows runs 32 bit and won't support the AMD 64 so you need either Linux or a long wait for Longhorn in 2006. Also few games are being made in 64 bit so it's currently an overkill. However AMD has alwasy been the supreme processor when it came to gaming, and with Longhorn it could truly redefine the world of computers. Although, p4's new technology will give you a "revolutionary experience, a new apex in processing speed".
<br />

<br />
Comments/Info/Suggestions..<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
